@ktiedt I briefly looked into mirroring that kind of functionality and the TLDR is.

* I couldn't find a way to do the animation (maybe private API?, or maybe I'm blind and missed the docs?) üòÜ 
* You can replicate the brightness and volume sliders with some craftily placed spacers in the popover touchbar

Thanks @MarshallOfSound for the awesome TouchBar support! Was wondering if someone tried a button with an image? I rebuilt the default app with the button below (in `default_app.js`), but it won't show up in the touch bar. Maybe some special image format/size is required? I could just find "2x with a maximum height of 30 points (corresponding to 60 pixels)" [in these docs](https://developer.apple.com/reference/appkit/nstouchbar#2647104).

```
const imageButton = new (TouchBar.Button)({
    image: path.join(__dirname, 'myimage@2x.png'),
    click: () => {
        console.log('my image clicked');
    }
});
```

Nice job @MarshallOfSound and @kevinsawicki ! I will retry a button with an image file, this did not work for me a few weeks back, likely because of my png. Maybe add an example with a working image?

```
const imageButton = new (TouchBar.Button)({
    image: path.join(__dirname, 'my-icon.png'),
    click: () => {
        console.log('my image clicked');
    }
});
```
